<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="put-off">put off</h1>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-delay-postpone">1.★ <strong>延期；推迟 (delay / postpone)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She called this afternoon to put off the meeting to next week. 
她下午打电话说把会议推迟到下周。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>使反感；使不信任：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is very clever but her manner does tend to put people off. 
她很聪明，但态度令人反感。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>打扰；使分心：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t put me off when I’m trying to concentrate. 
在我想要集中精力的时候别打扰我。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>使对...失去兴趣：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t let your failures put you off trying harder.
别因为失败你就不再进一步努力了。</p></div></div>